race.comment: ABSTRACTED (5) is running out of chances but her on-speed effort at Northam last time reads well in this lineup. She appears back on track and draws handy. ONE SHOT WONDER (9) won a Lark Hill trial but disappointed on the Pinjarra Scarpside on debut with today's race rider - the in-form CJP - aboard. Found a place in a recent Lark Hill trial and it won't surprise to see him come back improved and race boldly for the in-form stable. CHINESE DENTIST (2) was plain last time but he'd resumed in good order prior beaten 1.4L. Has a wide gate to manage but keeps the 3kg claim and can improve into the money with average luck in the run. BIG BOPPER (1) comes out of the same race and didn't get into it from a wide barrier. He resumed prior improved and expect him to use the inside gate today. Has claims with the extra fitness.
